Sir Adegoke Ogunwusi aka Sir Demola, Dele Gold, and five other music acts are set to embark on a musical tour of the United States of America and Canada. Sir Demola, who has five albums to his credit, is embarking on the tour with other music acts in collaboration with Samuel Ekundayo owned Sammek moments arts and cultural entertainment. Speaking more on the tour, Ekundayo said it was organised to promote the arts and culture. He also confirmed that six artists have been billed to also perform alongside Sir Demola on the tour,   King Promise thrills at Trace Live     How I deal with heartbreak, by Grace Agbo     Obi Cubana grateful to God at 47   The six other acts include Dele Gold, Laolu Gbenjo, Babatunde Balogun (Saxtee vibes), Boye Best, Segun Nabi, and Demola Suzi. According to the Sammek boss, the first leg of the musical tour will see the music acts performing at the Alujo Nite at Atlanta Event Centre Opera; Annual AHBCA Award at Expo Event Centre, Houston, Texas; Ijoko Agaba Nite at Kings Banquet Hall, Milwaukee; Ankara Nite in Texas; Annual Yoruba Cultural Festival in Howel, Miami. Headlining the tour, Sir Demola has performed to the admiration of several music lovers of Highlife and Juju music. Over the years, Sir Demolaâ€™s singing prowess has earned himself numerous awards both locally and internationally.